&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To advance&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href=&quot;https://teachforall.org/our-purpose&quot;&gt;Teach For All’s 25-year vision&lt;/a&gt;, we are seeking a strategic AI leader developer to join our Technology &amp;amp; Innovation team and work globally to identify and implement transformative technology solutions to accelerate the impact of our global network.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will &lt;strong&gt;work across the network with partners or groups of partners in order to identify and deliver transformative AI-forward&amp;nbsp; technology products to accelerate network impact&lt;/strong&gt;, as well as &lt;strong&gt;internally across the global organization to increase efficiency and effectiveness of our work&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp; The successful candidate will also be responsible for &lt;strong&gt;helping build and cultivate a community of technology enthusiasts across the network made up of network staff members, fellows and alumni&lt;/strong&gt; who will contribute to these projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Technology &amp;amp; Innovation Team provides &lt;strong&gt;thought-leadership and solutions&lt;/strong&gt; as well as &lt;strong&gt;foundational support&lt;/strong&gt; in the use of technology to unlock potential and accelerate impact &lt;strong&gt;across the organization and the global network&lt;/strong&gt;. The team leverages a deep understanding of the work and needs of the global organization, its teams and partners, our own expertise and global best practice to provide targeted solutions and technologies to accelerate our global impact. You will play a key role in this work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outcomes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identifying and delivering key AI-forward technologies for network partners&lt;/strong&gt; to support their work.&amp;nbsp; These may include tools for common needs across the network – classroom data collection, professional development of fellows, scheduling and management of Assessment Centers (where teaching fellows are selected) or new platforms (connectivity tools, online learning) -&amp;nbsp; which are identified and scoped in partnership with our network partners. Many if not all of these technologies will include AI components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Similarly, identifying and delivering technology solutions to increase the impact of the global organization. &lt;/strong&gt;This could include improvements to our&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;learning portals for network staff, fellows and alumni, an online platform enabling teachers and teacher coaches across and beyond our network to engage in our global professional development learning community, or a new global “constituent voice” system that enables all our network partners to surface feedback from key constituents in ways that strengthen global learning loops.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Taking an AI-forward approach &lt;/strong&gt;to increase organizational effectiveness, increase our impact in supporting network partners in their work, and evolve our systems and ways of working to incorporate new tools and technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Successful management of two solutions engineers and a UI/UX specialist&lt;/strong&gt; to deliver your ambitious strategy and goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy Development&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working across network partners and internal stakeholders including our AI and Ed Tech Initiative team to build context and identify key potential technology solutions to accelerate impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing a responsive and evolving strategy to prioritize and develop these key technologies,

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To advance&lt;a href=&quot;https://teachforall.org/our-purpose&quot;&gt; Teach For All’s 25-year vision&lt;/a&gt;, we are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Leadership Director for our Global Leadership Accelerator (GLA)&lt;/strong&gt;. The Accelerator works to grow the leadership of tens of thousands of leaders reshaping education around the world. This includes hundreds of staff supporting 15,000+ teachers currently in classrooms and close to 125,000 alumni leaders, collectively reaching millions of children across more than 60 countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join an entrepreneurial team accelerating the leadership and impact of thousands of social entrepreneurs, teachers, and system leaders who are reshaping education around the world. In this role, you will design transformative leadership experiences, coach senior leaders, and facilitate leadership development through both the &lt;strong&gt;Global Leadership Accelerator&lt;/strong&gt; and the &lt;strong&gt;Global Institute for Shaping a Better Future&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report directly to the Head of the Global Leadership Accelerator, who also serves as a Chief Learning Officer for the Global Institute for Shaping a Better Future.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
